DESCRIPTION:“Inclusive design” isn't just a buzzword\, it's built into our walls.\n\nWhile most of our guided walks focus on exhibitions\, this session offers something different—a chance to explore how the MAP building is designed to be inclusive and accessible for everyone. This one-hour walkthrough will be led by Inclusion Manager Shailesh Kulal\, who will share firsthand perspectives on accessibility and inclusive design.\n\nThis event is part of our International Day of Persons with Disabilities (IDPD) celebrations\, running from December 6\, 2025 onwards at MAP. The programme celebrates diverse abilities and aims to raise awareness\, promote accessibility\, and create inclusive environments in workplaces and communities.
